audiodecoder.name: AudioDecoder
audiodecoder.summary: The AudioDecoder() constructor creates a new AudioDecoder object with the provided init.output callback assigned as the output callback, the provided init.error callback as the error callback, and the AudioDecoder.state set to "unconfigured".
audiodecoder.title: AudioDecoder.AudioDecoder()

dom-audiodecoder-close.name: close
dom-audiodecoder-close.summary: The close() method of the AudioDecoder interface ends all pending work and releases system resources.

dom-audiodecoder-configure.name: configure
dom-audiodecoder-configure.summary: The configure() method of the AudioDecoder interface enqueues a control message to configure the audio decoder for decoding chunks.

dom-audiodecoder-decode.name: decode
dom-audiodecoder-decode.summary: The decode() method of the AudioDecoder interface enqueues a control message to decode a given chunk of audio.

dom-audiodecoder-flush.name: flush
dom-audiodecoder-flush.summary: The flush() method of the AudioDecoder interface returns a Promise that resolves once all pending messages in the queue have been completed.
dom-audiodecoder-flush.title: AudioDecoder.flush()

dom-audiodecoder-reset.name: reset
dom-audiodecoder-reset.summary: The reset() method of the AudioDecoder interface resets all states including configuration, control messages in the control message queue, and all pending callbacks.
dom-audiodecoder-reset.title: AudioDecoder.reset()

dom-audiodecoder-state.name: state
